## Testing Checklist

When making changes, verify:
- [ ] Screen lock detection works (lock screen manually)
- [ ] Screen unlock detection works (unlock screen)
- [ ] System sleep detection works (close laptop lid)
- [ ] System wake detection works (open laptop lid)
- [ ] Manual lap control works (Start New Lap button)
- [ ] Manual pause works (Stop button, minimum 3 seconds)
- [ ] State persists across app restarts
- [ ] Timers display smoothly without jumps
- [ ] Old state files load correctly
- [ ] Today's date validation works (yesterday's session doesn't restore)
- [ ] User manual pause is respected (no auto-resume on unlock)
- [ ] Startup notification shows after system restart with paused session
- [ ] Notification click starts tracking correctly

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

1. **Don't use `Instant` for persistence** - Use SystemTime and convert to Unix timestamps
2. **Don't forget to save state** - Call `save_state()` after state modifications
3. **Don't acquire multiple locks** - Can cause deadlocks, drop guards promptly
4. **Don't ignore user_paused flag** - Respect user's manual pause intent
5. **Don't add current lap to total_session_duration** - Backend should only have completed laps
6. **Don't poll too frequently** - 200ms is enough for smooth display
7. **Don't assume date is today** - Always validate date when loading state

## macOS-Specific Considerations

- Uses Objective-C/Cocoa APIs via `objc` and `cocoa` crates
- Screen lock detection uses `NSWorkspace.sharedWorkspace.frontmostApplication`
- Fallback methods: AppleScript queries, process checking
- Minimum macOS version: 10.13 (High Sierra)
- Will need adaptation for Windows/Linux support

